message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Tajikistan in the past five years was the completion and inauguration of the Rogun Dam in November 2018. The Rogun Dam is a major hydroelectric power project located on the Vakhsh River, and it is considered to be one of the world's tallest dams. The completion of this project was a significant milestone for Tajikistan as it aims to become a major exporter of electricity in the region. The dam has the potential to provide a stable source of energy for the country and contribute to its economic development.
